{
  "texts": [
    "These two equations can easily be combined to isolate F M and F Mμ:",
    "where we have defined A = M × μ.",
    "This method is illustrated in panels (d) and (f) of Fig. 19.",
    "In addition, any decomposition should verify F M > 0 and F Mμ > 0.",
    "In general, these two equations can be verified for a range of (positive) values of (M, μ)."
  ]
}